cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use GENOME or its benchmark results, please cite it as below."
title: "GENOME: a zero-LLM-call, bi-temporal memory layer for AI agents"
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Northtek (FrostByte Digital LLC)"
    email: info@northtek.io
repository-code: "https://github.com/NORTHTEKDevs/genome"
license: Apache-2.0
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-07-13
keywords:
  - agent memory
  - retrieval
  - bi-temporal
  - LoCoMo
  - LongMemEval
  - MCP
abstract: >-
  GENOME is a memory layer for AI agents that ingests with zero LLM calls
  (local embedding write path, ~10 ms/message, runs air-gapped), matches
  LLM-extraction memory (Mem0) on answer accuracy on LoCoMo and LongMemEval,
  and maintains a deterministic bi-temporal belief-state that answers
  point-in-time queries with full provenance. Benchmarks are within-harness
  with paired significance tests; null results are reported.
